article.description: Freshman guard Katie Rutan scored a season-high 25 points in her first career start, leading Xavier to a 92-50 victory over Saint Louis.
article.headline: Rutan's 25 points spark Musketeers' rout of Billikens
article.linkText: Xavier gets 12th straight win over Saint Louis
article.story:
CINCINNATI -- Freshman guard Katie Rutan scored a season-high 25 points in her first career start, leading Xavier (No. 10 ESPN/USA Today, No. 11 AP) to a 92-50 victory over Saint Louis on Wednesday night.

Rutan was 7-for-10 from 3-point range for the Musketeers (13-3, 3-0 Atlantic 10) in their 12th consecutive win over the Billikens (7-12, 1/3 A-10). She had six 3-pointers and 20 points at halftime.

Special Jennings added 16 points, and Amber Harris had 12 for Xavier.

Kathryn Hester led Saint Louis with 18 points.
